# TODO

* ipnet parser updates:
  - https://github.com/krisprice/ipnet/issues/32
  - https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/83652/files

* on the next database scheme change add `ON DELETE CASCADE` constraints to improve cleanup

* AI review:

  `try_madvise_dodump` now aligns the range to page boundaries, but
  MADV_DODUMP applies at page granularity and is not reference-counted.
  If multiple SecureVec allocations (or other sensitive allocations) share
  a page, dropping one buffer can re-enable dumping for a page that still
  contains live secrets. Consider avoiding MADV_DODUMP entirely, or
  implementing page-level refcounting / using page-aligned dedicated
  mappings so reverting doesn’t affect unrelated data.

* proxy without caching on quota hit?
* verify checksums of downloaded files (on, off, lazy)
* add option to limit archs (default: Dpkg::Arch::get_valid_arches())
* cache package list files and prefetch them every 30min?
* add option to import packages locally

