# Release workflow

   1.  check open GitHub issues
   2.  check open GitHub pull-requests
   3.  run `cargo update --verbose`
   4.  run `cargo outdated`
   5.  run `cargo deny check`
   6.  run `cargo audit`
   7.  run `typos`
   8.  run `codespell -L crate src/ debian/ deny.toml apt-cacher-rs.init README.md TODO`
   9.  run `cargo clippy`
  10.  run `cargo +nightly clippy`
  11.  update version in *Cargo.toml* and *debian/changelog*, then run `cargo check` (to update *Cargo.lock*)
  12.  create release commit with changed version number in *Cargo.toml* and *Cargo.lock*
  13.  run `cargo publish --dry-run`
  14.  run `cargo publish`
  15.  create git tag: `git tag -a -s -m "apt-cacher-rs Release 0.0.0" v0.0.0`
  16.  push git tag: `git push origin v0.0.0`
  17.  wait for *Generate Debian Package* workflow to succeed and generate Release Draft
  18.  publish the draft Release on GitHub
